                        <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://www.dvb.org/"><strong>http://www.dvb.org/</strong></a><strong>, 28 Mar 2003</strong> - European standardization policy has been brought up to date today as the result of the adoption of new guidelines between the European Commission (EC), the European Free Trade Association (EFTA), and the three official European Standards Organizations (ESOs).</font></p>
                        <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><em>For the full press release announced by the Digital Video Broadcasting Project, see: <a href="http://www.dvb.org/index.php?id=10&nid=24" target="_off">http://www.dvb.org/index.php?id=10&amp;nid=24</a></em></font><br>
